A chieftain of the People’s Democratic Party(PDP), Hon Hellen Taiwo-Adebakin has congratulated Chief Taiwo Abayomi Kuye on the occasion of his 70th birthday. Adebakin described Kuye, former organising Secretary of  PDP  in Lagos State and later caretaker  South-West of the PDP as a worthy who had made huge personal  sacrifice  for the growth and sustenance of the party. The PDP chieftain  said Kuye as the  leader  of the party remains a shining example for the younger generation in politics and leadership. Again, CSO Pressurizes Buhari To Assent To Electoral Act… Omosehin Promises Healthcare, Empowerment For Underprivileged In… “Today, I am celebrating our true leader and icon  of our party, Chief Kuye who is celebrating  his 70th birthday. It is a thing of joy seeing you attaining this age and I also pray that you witness many more of the day in good health. You have provided quality leadership in our party in South-West in particular and in Nigeria as whole.” “I am glad to identify with you as celebrate another milestone in your life. Happy birthday  to you our leader, father and mentor. May God Almighty continues to strengthens you as you mark more glorious years ahead”, Adebakin said.